pageContext.claim: “As you know, we have a very low rate of unemployment -- record-setting. We're at about 3.5, maybe 3.6. I hear it's going down -- probably will -- because the country is doing tremendous business.”
pageContext.analysis: At the time Trump spoke, the unemployment rate was 3.7 percent for June -- and then the government a few days later announced it was 3.7 percent in July.
